The paper discusses approaches towards making Linked Data accessible and useful for users without knowledge of formal query languages, specifically through question answering. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Given that the paper evaluates both a visual approach and natural language-based systems for question answering, it is likely to be relevant to researchers in all of these sub-categories.
